Comment (policies/secretsmanager_confidential_disposal_record.rego:112):
**Same runtime `eval_conflict_error` as `secretsmanager_access_administration_events.rego` (medium).** The six `event_secret_id` bodies (lines 73-106) here are the same shape as the access-administration policy and have the same runtime-error mode: a CloudTrail `DeleteSecret` event that populates both `requestParameters.secretId` and `resources[].ARN` (the default CloudTrail shape) makes `event_secret_id` produce two outputs for one input, and OPA aborts evaluation. `delete_secret_events` at this line consumes that broken helper, so every downstream violation (`disposal_authorisation_tag_missing`, `disposal_event_unattributable`, `unrecorded_administration`) is unreachable for realistic disposal evidence.

Suggested fix: same as the sibling thread — convert `event_secret_id` to a set-valued helper and change `event_matches_secret` to membership in that set. Cover with a regression test that populates both shapes on the same DeleteSecret event.
